# ------------------------------------------------------------
# How to Install External Libraries
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Navigate to the folder where the requirements.txt file exists:
#       cd <path-to-requirements-file>
# 2. Add all required libraries along with their versions to this file.
# 3. Install all dependencies using:
#       pip install -r requirements.txt
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# How to Activate a Virtual Environment (venv)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Navigate to your project root directory:
#       cd <project-root-folder>
# 2. Enter the virtual environment folder:
#       cd .venv
# 3. Go into the 'bin' directory:
#       cd bin
# 4. Activate the virtual environment:
#       macOS/Linux:  source activate
#       Windows:      activate
#
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# How to Generate a requirements.txt File
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Run the following command to capture installed package versions:
#       pip freeze > requirements.txt